WEBVTT

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:00:26.401 --> 00:00:27.402
{\an8}It's from Kuroi.

00:00:30.780 --> 00:00:32.032
What should we do?

00:00:32.991 --> 00:00:33.992
Kuroi...

00:00:34.743 --> 00:00:36.036
Kuroi, she...

00:00:38.329 --> 00:00:40.331
We should be prepared for
a worst-case senario.

00:00:40.915 --> 00:00:42.125
Mr. Geto, you are faster.

00:00:42.709 --> 00:00:44.502
Please go to Miss first.

00:00:47.839 --> 00:00:50.258
{\an8}I'm sorry, it was my negligence.

00:00:50.341 --> 00:00:51.718
Really?

00:00:51.801 --> 00:00:54.095
This isn't really
serious negligence, is it?

00:00:54.179 --> 00:00:57.515
I underestimated
Miss Kuroi's value to the enemy.

00:00:58.141 --> 00:00:59.517
{\an8}The enemy

00:00:59.601 --> 00:01:01.519
{\an8}will probably demand
for a hostage exchange.

00:01:02.604 --> 00:01:04.856
For example, to exchange
Amanai for Miss Kuroi,

00:01:04.939 --> 00:01:08.026
or to threaten us that they will kill
Miss Kuroi if we don't kill Amanai.

00:01:09.110 --> 00:01:12.489
But we have Amanai here, so we have
the upper hand in the negotiation.

00:01:13.114 --> 00:01:15.408
If we could just decide on
the place to meet them,

00:01:15.492 --> 00:01:17.535
we will find a way.

00:01:18.328 --> 00:01:20.914
Amanai should be taken
straight to the high school,

00:01:20.997 --> 00:01:22.957
and we'll have Shoko or
someone to be her double.

00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:24.000
Wait.

00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:27.212
I will go to the trading site.

00:01:27.295 --> 00:01:29.005
I still don't trust you guys.

00:01:29.088 --> 00:01:29.923
Huh?

00:01:30.006 --> 00:01:31.591
You brat, this isn't the time for...

00:01:31.674 --> 00:01:33.551
Even if you successfully rescue Kuroi,

00:01:34.344 --> 00:01:38.723
if she can't come back before
I merge with Master Tengen...

00:01:39.933 --> 00:01:41.100
I...

00:01:44.354 --> 00:01:46.314
I haven't even said goodbye to her.

00:01:57.408 --> 00:01:59.869
The kidnapper should contact us soon.

00:02:00.829 --> 00:02:03.873
But if the enemy is smarter than expected,

00:02:03.957 --> 00:02:08.253
and taking you with us would lower
Miss Kuroi's survival rate...

00:02:12.257 --> 00:02:14.342
then we will go without you.

00:02:22.600 --> 00:02:23.852
{\an8}Alright,

00:02:23.935 --> 00:02:25.520
{\an8}that's fine.

00:02:26.271 --> 00:02:27.939
{\an8}Conversely,

00:02:28.022 --> 00:02:31.568
{\an8}even if you want to go back halfway
because you're scared, we won't care.

00:02:32.443 --> 00:02:34.028
{\an8}Be prepared.

00:02:39.534 --> 00:02:42.036
- Here we are!
- Here we are!

00:02:46.332 --> 00:02:48.960
{\an8}PROTECTING AMANAI DAY 2

00:02:49.043 --> 00:02:51.963
OKINAWA

00:04:30.687 --> 00:04:34.899
I didn't expect that I would be fooled by
a non-sorcerer of Star Religious Group...

00:04:35.483 --> 00:04:37.402
It's so embarrassing.

00:04:37.485 --> 00:04:40.238
It's understandable
since it was an ambush.

00:04:40.321 --> 00:04:41.906
I'm also to blame.

00:04:42.657 --> 00:04:45.618
{\an8}Was it... really an ambush?

00:04:47.245 --> 00:04:48.830
<i>After the Q incident,</i>

00:04:48.913 --> 00:04:51.291
<i>I have been on high alert...</i>

00:04:52.375 --> 00:04:53.501
Kuroi!

00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:58.339
{\an8}But I still can't remember
how I was attacked...

00:04:59.340 --> 00:05:01.926
Anyway, you guys came by plane, right?

00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:04.887
Was there any problem?
Did you meet any enemy...

00:05:05.471 --> 00:05:07.015
Satoru has good eyes.

00:05:08.766 --> 00:05:11.394
<i>He checked the passengers and crews,</i>

00:05:13.187 --> 00:05:15.606
<i>as well as the inside and
outside the plane before takeoff.</i>

00:05:16.190 --> 00:05:19.569
<i>During the flight,
my cursed spirit was on guard outside.</i>

00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:23.948
<i>It's safer than traveling by land.</i>

00:05:25.658 --> 00:05:27.410
{\an8}What I want to know is,

00:05:27.493 --> 00:05:30.580
{\an8}why would they specify
Okinawa as the location.

00:05:31.164 --> 00:05:33.082
Are they trying to buy time?

00:05:33.708 --> 00:05:35.668
Even if they can't kill Miss Riko,

00:05:35.752 --> 00:05:38.087
they want to make sure
we miss tomorrow's full moon.

00:05:38.171 --> 00:05:39.797
If that's the case,

00:05:39.881 --> 00:05:43.051
they would choose a remote area
where transportation is inconvenient.

00:05:43.634 --> 00:05:46.763
They won't take over
the airport, will they?

00:05:46.846 --> 00:05:49.057
Maybe, but it doesn't matter.

00:05:49.766 --> 00:05:52.643
<i>We are not the only ones who came here.</i>

00:05:54.687 --> 00:05:56.355
No matter how you look at it,

00:05:56.439 --> 00:05:58.733
this isn't a mission for the first years.

00:05:58.816 --> 00:06:01.110
I feel very excited!

00:06:01.194 --> 00:06:03.571
I want to show Geto how good I am.

00:06:03.654 --> 00:06:06.282
Moreover, the seniors are fighting hard

00:06:06.365 --> 00:06:09.160
to protect a vulnerable girl.

00:06:09.243 --> 00:06:11.621
How could we not work hard?

00:06:12.622 --> 00:06:16.375
If a typhoon comes and the airport is
closed, all our efforts will be in vain.

00:06:17.794 --> 00:06:19.295
THE HARDWORKING SENIOR

00:06:19.378 --> 00:06:20.296
Sea cucumber!

00:06:20.379 --> 00:06:23.257
Gross, it's so gross!

00:06:24.675 --> 00:06:26.928
Is it really okay for us
to come sightseeing?

00:06:27.011 --> 00:06:28.805
This is Satoru's suggestion.

00:06:29.722 --> 00:06:32.683
He is also caring for Riko in his own way.

00:06:33.935 --> 00:06:35.186
But we should be going now.

00:06:36.312 --> 00:06:37.980
Satoru, it's time.

00:06:38.606 --> 00:06:40.191
Already?

00:06:45.780 --> 00:06:48.574
Suguru, let's go back tomorrow morning.

00:06:51.452 --> 00:06:52.328
But...

00:06:52.912 --> 00:06:54.789
The weather is stable, right?

00:06:56.207 --> 00:06:57.542
Moreover...

00:06:57.625 --> 00:06:59.877
Compared to Tokyo, here in Okinawa...

00:07:00.461 --> 00:07:02.004
there are fewer curse users.

00:07:02.088 --> 00:07:04.257
Can we talk seriously, Satoru?

00:07:05.258 --> 00:07:08.469
It'd be better
if Amanai's bounty ends during our flight.

00:07:08.553 --> 00:07:09.971
Look, a starfish.

00:07:10.054 --> 00:07:11.347
Satoru,

00:07:11.431 --> 00:07:13.766
{\an8}you haven't dismantled
the Cursed Technique since yesterday.

00:07:13.850 --> 00:07:15.518
{\an8}And you haven't slept at all.

00:07:15.601 --> 00:07:17.270
{\an8}You don't plan to sleep tonight either.

00:07:17.895 --> 00:07:20.773
{\an8}Is it really okay that
we don't go back to the high school?

00:07:22.859 --> 00:07:24.777
It's fine.

00:07:24.861 --> 00:07:28.364
I felt more tired when
I played <i>Momotetsu '99</i>.

00:07:30.158 --> 00:07:31.451
And...

00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:32.785
you're here too.

00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:40.334
Nanami,

00:07:40.418 --> 00:07:42.336
I heard they are staying an extra day.

00:07:42.420 --> 00:07:43.713
Did something happen?

00:09:30.736 --> 00:09:32.905
TOKYO JUJUTSU HIGH SCHOOL
MUSHIROYAMA FOOTHILLS

00:09:34.448 --> 00:09:37.326
PROTECTING AMANAI DAY 3, 15:00

00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.161
Great job, everyone.

00:09:41.747 --> 00:09:43.749
This place is inside the school's barrier.

00:09:45.334 --> 00:09:47.253
Now we can rest assured.

00:09:47.336 --> 00:09:48.212
Yes.

00:09:50.548 --> 00:09:51.382
Satoru,

00:09:53.301 --> 00:09:54.969
good job.

00:09:58.723 --> 00:09:59.974
I'll never do babysitting

00:10:00.057 --> 00:10:01.684
ever again.

00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:13.112
{\an8}<i>Impossible.</i>

00:10:13.195 --> 00:10:14.780
{\an8}<i>This is...</i>

00:10:14.864 --> 00:10:17.199
{\an8}<i>inside the school's barrier!</i>

00:10:17.783 --> 00:10:19.201
Have I...

00:10:19.285 --> 00:10:20.953
seen you somewhere before?

00:10:21.037 --> 00:10:24.332
{\an8}Don't mind it, because I'm the same.

00:10:24.415 --> 00:10:26.959
{\an8}I'm not good at remembering men's names.

00:10:30.880 --> 00:10:33.507
<i>I once went to see that Six-Eyed kid</i>

00:10:33.591 --> 00:10:36.135
<i>born into the Gojo family
out of curiosity.</i>

00:10:56.155 --> 00:10:57.823
<i>It was the first and last time</i>

00:10:57.907 --> 00:11:00.493
{\an8}<i>anyone notices
that I'm standing behind them.</i>

00:11:00.576 --> 00:11:02.536
{\an8}<i>It was the only time.</i>

00:11:03.037 --> 00:11:05.206
<i>So I weakened your spirit,</i>

00:11:10.252 --> 00:11:12.129
<i>until you became dull.</i>

00:11:22.264 --> 00:11:23.265
Satoru!

00:11:24.767 --> 00:11:26.185
I'm okay.

00:11:26.685 --> 00:11:29.647
I couldn't use a cursed technique in time,
but it didn't hit my vital organs.

00:11:30.231 --> 00:11:32.149
I used cursed energy
to strengthen my body,

00:11:32.233 --> 00:11:34.110
so that the blade
wouldn't hurt other parts.

00:11:35.152 --> 00:11:38.823
It's just like a safety pin
going through a sweater.

00:11:39.532 --> 00:11:41.033
I'm really okay.

00:11:41.117 --> 00:11:43.786
Don't mind me and go protect Amanai.

00:11:44.370 --> 00:11:46.122
Leave this guy to me.

00:11:46.831 --> 00:11:50.668
You guys go to Master Tengen first.

00:11:52.294 --> 00:11:53.337
Satoru...

00:11:58.843 --> 00:12:00.928
Be careful.

00:12:01.011 --> 00:12:02.304
Let's go.

00:12:02.388 --> 00:12:03.264
Yes.

00:12:04.098 --> 00:12:05.933
Who do you think you're talking to?

00:12:13.315 --> 00:12:16.318
<i>That's not the sword
he stabbed me with just now.</i>

00:12:16.902 --> 00:12:18.779
<i>Where did that cursed spirit come from?</i>

00:12:19.780 --> 00:12:22.158
<i>I can't figure him out, damn it.</i>

00:12:22.867 --> 00:12:24.785
The Star Plasma Vessel isn't here.

00:12:25.286 --> 00:12:28.622
I was hoping to kill you with that.

00:12:28.706 --> 00:12:29.707
Have my skills declined?

00:12:29.790 --> 00:12:33.210
The bounty on Amana
has been withdrawn, you fool.

00:12:33.294 --> 00:12:36.213
It was me who withdrew it, you bluffer.

00:12:36.839 --> 00:12:39.133
To deal with a flawless guy like you,

00:12:39.216 --> 00:12:42.553
I have to focus on pace and
set up a few false endpoints.

00:12:43.053 --> 00:12:47.475
When the Star Religious Group
went to Okinawa, it made me laugh.

00:12:47.558 --> 00:12:51.145
You didn't lose a single sorcerer
by your side, that really annoys me.

00:12:51.228 --> 00:12:54.148
But if I hadn't set a time
limit for the bounty,

00:12:54.732 --> 00:12:58.110
you wouldn't dismantle
until the very last moment probably.

00:12:58.777 --> 00:13:00.112
Whatever.

00:13:05.993 --> 00:13:07.495
<i>So fast.</i>

00:13:07.578 --> 00:13:08.829
<i>Not just fast.</i>

00:13:09.413 --> 00:13:11.832
<i>There is something off about this guy.</i>

00:13:11.916 --> 00:13:13.834
{\an8}<i>He has absolutely no cursed energy.</i>

00:13:14.585 --> 00:13:17.463
<i>This is a physical talent
of Heavenly Restriction.</i>

00:13:49.870 --> 00:13:53.249
<i>People who understand
my technique wouldn't act recklessly.</i>

00:13:53.958 --> 00:13:55.751
Is that cursed tool your trump card?

00:13:55.834 --> 00:13:58.337
I'm sorry, but I won't let
you get any closer to me.

00:14:13.769 --> 00:14:16.313
<i>Because he has no cursed energy,
I can't feel his presence.</i>

00:14:16.397 --> 00:14:19.316
{\an8}<i>I can only rely on intuition...
No there's a way.</i>

00:14:19.900 --> 00:14:21.652
<i>That cursed spirit is on his body.</i>

00:14:22.194 --> 00:14:24.530
{\an8}<i>I just need to track that.</i>

00:14:26.657 --> 00:14:27.741
<i>Anyway,</i>

00:14:28.701 --> 00:14:30.077
<i>isn't he a bit too fast?</i>

00:14:30.828 --> 00:14:31.954
<i>Cursed Technique Lapse.</i>

00:14:33.289 --> 00:14:34.790
Maximum output.

00:14:40.713 --> 00:14:41.672
Blue.

00:14:56.353 --> 00:14:58.022
<i>Without cover,</i>

00:14:58.105 --> 00:14:59.773
<i>he can't launch a surprise attack.</i>

00:14:59.857 --> 00:15:01.317
<i>Did he hide in the forest?</i>

00:15:03.861 --> 00:15:04.820
<i>Those are...</i>

00:15:06.530 --> 00:15:07.573
<i>Fly Heads?!</i>

00:15:11.785 --> 00:15:14.455
{\an8}<i>Did he breed these inside
that cursed spirit's body?</i>

00:15:14.538 --> 00:15:17.207
Using the Fly Heads as chaff?

00:15:17.875 --> 00:15:19.752
<i>Now I can't locate him.</i>

00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:22.963
<i>And he's created blind spots.</i>

00:15:23.047 --> 00:15:24.506
<i>I'll cast Blue again...</i>

00:15:25.049 --> 00:15:26.592
<i>No, wait.</i>

00:15:26.675 --> 00:15:28.093
<i>His target is...</i>

00:15:28.177 --> 00:15:29.219
<i>Amanai.</i>

00:15:36.226 --> 00:15:38.520
{\an8}<i>You're sharp enough to notice me
even with my hands empty.</i>

00:15:39.104 --> 00:15:41.607
<i>And with the Six Eyes,
you can't possibly miss...</i>

00:15:41.690 --> 00:15:44.568
<i>the heterogeneous cursed energy
seeping out of this cursed tool.</i>

00:15:46.153 --> 00:15:47.988
But you have finally...

00:15:50.741 --> 00:15:53.494
started to defend with cursed techniques.

00:16:26.318 --> 00:16:29.488
Special grade cursed tool,
Inverted Spear of Heaven.

00:16:29.571 --> 00:16:33.534
Its effect is to forcibly
dismantle any ongoing spells.

00:16:34.618 --> 00:16:35.494
I have gradually...

00:16:39.248 --> 00:16:40.916
regained my touch.

00:17:19.955 --> 00:17:21.165
Miss Riko,

00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:24.418
this is where we separate.

00:17:26.462 --> 00:17:29.506
Miss Riko, please...

00:17:34.011 --> 00:17:36.555
Kuroi, I like you the most.

00:17:37.139 --> 00:17:40.100
I always have, and I always will.

00:17:41.393 --> 00:17:42.311
And I...

00:17:42.978 --> 00:17:45.022
I like you the most too.

00:18:07.044 --> 00:18:08.212
This is the place...

00:18:08.295 --> 00:18:09.129
Yes.

00:18:09.213 --> 00:18:11.799
This is where Master Tengen is.

00:18:13.258 --> 00:18:15.260
This is the foundation of
major domestic barriers,

00:18:16.220 --> 00:18:18.055
the main hall of Tombs of the Star.

00:18:19.598 --> 00:18:23.143
After you descend the stairs
and pass through that gate,

00:18:23.227 --> 00:18:25.521
walk to the roots of that big tree.

00:18:26.105 --> 00:18:29.191
Unlike the barrier around the school,

00:18:29.274 --> 00:18:31.026
there is a special barrier,

00:18:31.610 --> 00:18:34.238
which only those invited can enter.

00:18:34.988 --> 00:18:38.158
Master Tengen will protect you,
until the merge is complete.

00:18:41.078 --> 00:18:42.621
{\an8}Or,

00:18:42.704 --> 00:18:45.457
{\an8}you can also turn back,
and go home with Miss Kuroi.

00:18:50.712 --> 00:18:54.133
When we heard about this
mission from our instructor,

00:18:54.216 --> 00:18:57.845
<i>he referred to merge as erase.</i>

00:18:57.928 --> 00:19:01.890
He meant we should feel guilty
about this mission.

00:19:02.474 --> 00:19:04.893
Though our instructor is a meathead,

00:19:04.977 --> 00:19:06.728
he often does things in a roundabout way.

00:19:10.816 --> 00:19:12.484
Before meeting you,

00:19:12.568 --> 00:19:14.987
<i>Satoru and I had agreed.</i>

00:19:17.406 --> 00:19:20.117
What if the Star Plasma Vessel
refuses to merge?

00:19:20.617 --> 00:19:22.411
Then...

00:19:22.494 --> 00:19:24.037
just don't merge.

00:19:25.706 --> 00:19:26.582
Is that okay?

00:19:28.125 --> 00:19:31.545
We might have to fight
against Master Tengen.

00:19:33.380 --> 00:19:35.048
Are you scared?

00:19:35.799 --> 00:19:38.260
Don't worry, there will be a way.

00:19:39.261 --> 00:19:41.180
We are the strongest.

00:19:42.389 --> 00:19:44.850
No matter what choice you make,

00:19:44.933 --> 00:19:47.519
we will secure your future.

00:19:51.815 --> 00:19:53.108
Since I was born...

00:19:53.859 --> 00:19:56.528
I've always been special,

00:19:56.612 --> 00:19:58.739
<i>and told that I'm different from others.</i>

00:20:00.824 --> 00:20:03.160
<i>For me, this kind of special
is actually quite normal.</i>

00:20:04.036 --> 00:20:06.205
<i>I avoid danger as much as possible,</i>

00:20:06.288 --> 00:20:07.956
<i>living till now for this day.</i>

00:20:09.666 --> 00:20:13.337
<i>I don't remember when my parents died,</i>

00:20:13.921 --> 00:20:16.173
<i>nor do I feel sad or lonely anymore.</i>

00:20:18.008 --> 00:20:19.426
<i>So I thought...</i>

00:20:19.509 --> 00:20:22.804
<i>even if I have to separate from everyone
for the sake of the merge, it's okay.</i>

00:20:26.433 --> 00:20:28.185
<i>No matter how painful it is,</i>

00:20:28.810 --> 00:20:32.272
<i>My sadness and loneliness will be gone.</i>

00:20:34.274 --> 00:20:37.069
<i>But...</i>

00:20:37.778 --> 00:20:39.571
<i>I still...</i>

00:20:39.655 --> 00:20:42.324
want to spend more time with everyone.

00:20:43.033 --> 00:20:47.287
I want to go to more places with them,

00:20:47.371 --> 00:20:49.039
and see all kinds of scenery...

00:20:50.666 --> 00:20:52.000
I want to...

00:20:52.584 --> 00:20:55.170
Let's go back, Riko.

00:21:19.653 --> 00:21:21.154
Riko?

00:21:22.072 --> 00:21:23.949
Alright, good job.

00:21:25.993 --> 00:21:28.120
You're dismissed.

00:21:32.791 --> 00:21:35.127
{\an8}Why are you here?

00:21:37.421 --> 00:21:38.755
Why?

00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:41.133
You mean that?

00:21:43.969 --> 00:21:47.055
I killed Satoru Gojo.

00:22:01.111 --> 00:22:02.237
Is that so?

00:22:03.071 --> 00:22:04.072
Die.

00:23:37.290 --> 00:23:40.794
<i>Although everyone says,
it's never too late to take a new step,</i>

00:23:40.877 --> 00:23:44.506
<i>the problem is often not when
to start, but when to stop.</i>

00:23:45.549 --> 00:23:47.384
<i>Next episode, Hidden Inventory Part 4.</i>

00:23:47.467 --> 00:23:50.262
<i>Please look forward to it... or maybe not.</i>

00:23:51.305 --> 00:24:51.356
